This project is an independent, unofficial implementation of the multi-model
"panel + judge + synthesis" methodology that OpenRouter describes and markets
under the name "Fusion". This project is NOT affiliated with, endorsed by, or
sponsored by OpenRouter. "Fusion" is used here only to credit and describe the
methodology; all trademarks belong to their respective owners.

alloy ships no API keys and makes no network calls of its own. It orchestrates
third-party command-line tools (for example OpenAI's `codex` and Google's
`gemini`) that you install and authenticate yourself. When alloy invokes those
tools, your prompts and any code you ask it to review are sent to those tools'
model providers under their terms. You are responsible for complying with each
tool's terms of service, including any restrictions on automated invocation.

Those CLIs and their trademarks belong to their respective owners and are not
distributed with this project.
